The White House Office of the Press Secretary expressed deep concern over recent reports of civilian deaths in Mokha, Yemen, as well as the deaths of volunteers from the Yemen Red Crescent Society in Taiz. The statement called on all sides of the conflict to avoid harming civilians and to comply with international humanitarian law. The United States emphasized that it has no role in the targeting decisions made by the Coalition in Yemen, but has consistently urged precise targeting and thorough investigations into credible allegations of civilian casualties. The statement also highlighted the need for a peaceful political dialogue to resolve the crisis in Yemen.